What are pods ?
Pods are the smalled unit in kubernetes which is used to deploy a container. Which provide high abstraction over a resource 

What are controllers?
Controller's keep's our app running in the desired state of the pod . Starting and stopping of the application and autoscaling check's deployment state 

What are static pod's?
BAsically static pods are something that are managed by kubectl node. A static pod runs because it's Yaml file exist on the node in the location called (/etc/kubernetes/manifest)
No deployment or Replicat set or scheduler. Kubectl watches the file and ensure the pod is always running . If the pod craches or the file is changed kubectl restart. Update it 

/var/lib/kubelet/config.yaml

